Executive Profile
J. Michael Losh  Independent Chairman, Masco CorporationAgeTotal Calculated CompensationThis person is connected to 7 Board Members in 7 different organizations across 11 different industries.See Board Relationships71$455,052
Background

		Mr. J. Michael Losh, also known as Mike, served as the Chief Financial Officer of Cardinal Health, Inc. from July 2004 to May 2005 and Interim Chief Financial Officer from July 26, 2004 to August 2004 and also served its Principal Accounting Officer. Mr. Losh was with General Motors from 1964 to 2000. He served as the Chief Financial Officer and Executive Vice President of General Motors Corp., the world's largest vehicle manufacturer from July 1994 to August 2000. He ... served as Vice President of General Motors and General Manager of the Pontiac Division since July 1984 and served as Vice President and General Manager of the Oldsmobile Division since June 1989. From 1992 to 1994, he served as Group Vice President in charge of North American Vehicle Sales, Service and Marketing. He oversaw major capacity expansion programs and integrated finance functions when he served as Finance Director of General Motors do Brazil from 1979 to 1982 and as Managing Director of General Motors de Mexico from 1982 to 1984. He is a Private Investor. He was employed at Motors Liquidation Company. Mr. Losh spent 36 years in various capacities with General Motors, where he served as Chairman of GMAC, its financial services group, from July 1994 to April 1999. He has been the Chairman of Masco Corporation since May 4, 2015. He served as the Chairman of Metaldyne Corp. from October 2000 to April 2002. He has been Independent Director of HB Fuller Co since 2001. He has been an Independent Director of Prologis, Inc. and TRW Automotive Holdings Corp. since January 2003 and November 21, 2003 respectively. Mr. Losh has been an Independent Director of AON plc since 2003. He has been a Director of Cardinal Health 414, LLC since 1996, H.B. Fuller Company since 2001, Masco Corporation. since November 3, 2003 and TRW Automotive Inc. since November 2003. He served as a Director of  TRW Automotive Aftermarket since January 2003 until May 15, 2015. He served as a Presiding Director of CareFusion Corporation since September 2009 and served as its Director since 2009 until March 17, 2015. He served as an Independent Director of AMB Property Corp., a General Partner of Prologis LP since 2003. Mr. Losh served as Director of Oldco M Corporation since November 28, 2000, Cardinal Health Inc. since 1996, Quaker Oats Company since 1998, Hughes Electronics from February 1995 to August 2000 and Delphi Automotive Systems Corp. since 1999. He served as Director of Ally Financial Inc., Care Fusion Inc., Electronic Data Systems Corporation and DIRECTV. He served as Member of the Advisory Board at Tanner & Haley Destination Clubs. Mr. Losh holds a B.S. in Mechanical Engineering from Kettering University and an M.B.A. from Harvard University.Read Full Background




